  "text": "Due to the deciency and side effects of current therapies for prostate cancer, more and more patients turn to dietary supplements, including vitamins, herbal preparations and phytochemicals to control the risk of PCa. [CITATION_1] Torulene, one of the most principal carotenoid in Sporidiobolus pararoseus, has 13 conjugated double bonds, and the differences of structure between it and lycopene are subtle. However, it has not been well-studied with respect to its bioactivity and nutritional function.",
